Given below is the program to count all the numbers which are divisible by 2,3 or 5 and are less than or equal to 30. \
Read the program carefully and find the correct output.
```
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int count = 0;

        for(int i = 1; i <= 30; i++) {
            if(i % 2 == 0) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count); // tracing count which stores number divisible by 2.

        for(int i = 1; i <= 30; i++) {
            if(i % 3 == 0 && i % 2 != 0) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count); // tracing count which stores number divisible by 2 and 3.

        for(int i = 1; i <= 30; i++) {
            if(i % 5 == 0 && i % 2 != 0 && i % 3 != 0) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(count); // final answer which stores number divisible by 2, 3, and 5
    }
}

```

